10. Termination and reinstatement

    10.1 Termination
        Any violation of this license automatically terminates the permissions granted to You.

    10.2 Reinstatement (cure)
        If You cease the violation and come into full compliance within 30 days of the earlier of:
            (i) Your receipt of notice of the violation from the Licensor; or
            (ii) the date You knew or reasonably should have known of the violation,
                the permissions granted to You are automatically reinstated.

        Automatic reinstatement does not apply if this is the third (or more) violation by You within
        any rolling 12-month period. In that case, reinstatement requires the Licensorâ€™s explicit
        written permission or a separate paid commercial license.

    10.3 Effect of termination
        Upon termination, You must immediately stop all Production Use unless and until You obtain
        a paid commercial license or fully satisfy option (B) while Production Use continues.

